    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363/34</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Liaison Officer</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alling</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-29">April 29,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Alling</hi>: At the meeting of the Liaison
                        Committee<note n="33" xml:id="d687fn33">Composed of the Chief of Staff,
                        Chief of Naval Operations, and the Under Secretary of State.</note> held on
                    Monday, April 27, the protection of the oil installations in Saudi Arabia was
                    considered. The representative of the War Department <pb facs="0589" n="577"
                        xml:id="pg_577"/> stated that that Department had at present no plans to
                    send any forces or equipment to the region in question. It is the belief that
                    while a possibility of an air raid on the oil fields of that region exists the
                    danger to the refineries on Bahrein Island is much greater.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Orme Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
